hands_on_practices.problem:
A computational biologist has developed a new algorithm, "GeneProspector," to identify candidate genes associated with a specific neurodegenerative disorder by analyzing a large gene co-expression network. The algorithm's output is a list of genes predicted to be involved in the disease. To validate the algorithm, this list is compared against a "gold-standard" set of genes already established to be causally linked to the disorder through experimental studies.

The GeneProspector algorithm predicted the following set of 7 genes:
{SNCA, LRRK2, PINK1, GBA, UCHL1, PARK7, HTRA2}

The gold-standard validation list consists of the following 20 known disease-related genes:
{SNCA, PARK7, PINK1, LRRK2, ATP13A2, FBXO7, GBA, PLA2G6, PRKN, SYNJ1, DNAJC6, VPS35, EIF4G1, GCH1, TH, SPR, DDC, MAPT, APOE, UCHL1}

Based on the provided lists, calculate the precision of the GeneProspector algorithm's prediction. Express your answer as a decimal value, rounded to three significant figures.
